HEADWORD: Engrailment
<hw>En*grail"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
ring of dots round the edge of a medal, etc.</def> <rj><au>Brande &
C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Indentation in curved lines, as of
a line of division or the edge of an ordinary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Engrain</ent>⟦br⟧
